{"id": 223698588, "title": "Letters, May 26: Trudeau Liberals' legalization of pot stinks", "text": "ANAS KHAN Beaumont (If nothing else, the strong odour of weed is offensive to most.) TRUDEAU BASHING I am not particularly a Trudeau fan. But it is getting rather tiresome reading and hearing Poilievre, Smith and many columnists and \u201carmchair wannabe politicians\u201d rant about the shortcomings of our PM. Yeah, he ain\u2019t perfect. But instead of a steady stream of criticisms, I would like to read or hear realistic solutions for climate change, the economy and foreign affairs. And please don\u2019t mention carbon capture \u2014 it doesn\u2019t work. Neither does leaving interest rates low tackle inflation. Finally, not sending funds to needy nations will ultimately come back to bite us all in the behind. Corporations and the wealthy have benefited far too long from tax loopholes, and not paying working Canadians adequate wages, which is primarily why the Canadian government has a \u201cspending problem.\u201d If they didn\u2019t pick up the slack, Canada would be one step closer to civil unrest. MARK PATTERSON (Poilievre may get his chance to offer alternative solutions after the next election.)", "summary": "VOTE IN OUR DAILY POLL: Do you visibly show support for the Oilers? CONTACT NONSENSE In the wake of BC\u2019s Government asking Trudeau to reconsider decriminalization of certain drugs, this contributor has to share this after thanking the Feds. Thank you Mr. PM and company to have legalized smoking of weed in public, one cannot [&#8230;]", "url": "https://edmontonsun.com/opinion/letters/letters-may-26-trudeau-liberals-legalization-of-pot-stinks", "image": "https://smartcdn.gprod.postmedia.digital/edmontonsun/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/trudeau-meeting.jpg?quality=100&strip=all", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 12:00:57", "author": "Barry Hanson,Edmonton Sun", "authors": ["Barry Hanson", "Edmonton Sun"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ca"